  "text": "In this paper, we will present a new approach to (1.2) based on considerations of η-invariants of Atiyah-Patodi-Singer [CITATION_1] . Besides giving a new proof of (1.2), our method also provides an extension of (1.2) to cover the real part of the Cheeger-Chern-Simons character. One of the main results of this paper can be stated as the following identity in H odd (B, R/Q),",
